Here's a Java solution to the problem that doesn't use loops or recursion:

```
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }
        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n /= 3;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
```

The solution uses a while loop to repeatedly divide n by 3 until it is no longer divisible by 3. If n is a power of three, then eventually n will be reduced to 1. We also check the base cases where n is less than or equal to 0, in which case it cannot be a power of three.

